      <td style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;"> <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; text-indent: -18pt;">Effect of exchange rate on cash and cash equivalents</p> </td>
      <td style="width: 1%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">&#xa0;</td>

  <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;">J &amp; J SNACK FOODS CORP. AND SUBSIDIARIES</p>
  <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;">NOTES TO THE CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS</p>
  <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;">(unaudited)</p>
  <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;">&#xa0;</p>
  <div>
    &#xa0;
  </div>
  <ix:nonNumeric contextRef="d_2019-09-29_2019-12-28" name="us-gaap:SignificantAccountingPoliciesTextBlock" id="c1406227" escape="true">
   <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width: 100%; text-indent: 0px;">
    <tbody>
     <tr style="vertical-align: top;">
      <td style="width: 54pt;"> <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">Note <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">1</em></p> </td>
      <td> <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">The accompanying unaudited Consolidated Financial Statements have been prepared in accordance with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States for interim financial information and with the instructions to Form&#xa0;<em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">10</em>-Q and Rule&#xa0;<em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">10</em>-<em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">01</em> of Regulation&#xa0;S-<em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">X.</em> They do <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">not</em> include all information and notes required by generally accepted accounting principles for complete financial statements. However, except as disclosed herein, there has been <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">no</em> material change in the information disclosed in the Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements included in the Company&#x2019;s Annual Report on Form&#xa0;<em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">10</em>-K &#xa0;for the year ended <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> September 28, 2019.</em></p> </td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">In the opinion of management, the accompanying unaudited consolidated financial statements contain all adjustments (consisting of only normal recurring adjustments) necessary to present fairly the financial position and the results of operations and cash flows.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">The results of operations for the <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">three</em> months ended <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> December 28, 2019 </em>and <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> December 29, 2018 </em>are <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">not</em> necessarily indicative of results for the full year. Sales of our frozen beverages and frozen juice bars and ices are generally higher in the <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">third</em> and <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">fourth</em> quarters due to warmer weather.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:54pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">Certain prior year financial statement amounts have been reclassified to be consistent with the presentation for the current year.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:54pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-54pt;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">While we believe that the disclosures presented are adequate to make the information <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">not</em> misleading, it is suggested that these consolidated financial statements be read in conjunction with the consolidated financial statements and the notes included in the Company&#x2019;s Annual Report on Form <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">10</em>-K for the fiscal year ended <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> September 28, 2019.</em></p>
  </ix:nonNumeric>
  <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
  <div>
    &#xa0;
  </div>
  <ix:nonNumeric contextRef="d_2019-09-29_2019-12-28" name="us-gaap:RevenueFromContractWithCustomerTextBlock" id="c1406228" escape="true">
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">Note <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">2</em></p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;">Revenue Recognition</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;"><b>&#xa0;</b></p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; ">When Performance Obligations Are Satisfied</span></p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">A performance obligation is a promise in a contract to transfer a distinct good or service to the customer and is the unit of account for revenue recognition. A contract&#x2019;s transaction price is allocated to each distinct performance obligation and recognized as revenue when, or as, the performance obligation is satisfied.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-4.5pt;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">The singular performance obligation of our customer contracts for product and machine sales is determined by each individual purchase order and the respective products ordered, with revenue being recognized at a point-in-time when the obligation under the terms of the agreement is satisfied and product control is transferred to our customer. Specifically, control transfers to our customers when the product is delivered to, installed or picked up by our customers based upon applicable shipping terms, as our customers can direct the use and obtain substantially all of the remaining benefits from the product at this point in time. The performance obligations in our customer contracts for product are generally satisfied within <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">30</em> days.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-4.5pt;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">The singular performance obligation of our customer contracts for time and material repair and maintenance equipment service is the performance of the repair and maintenance with revenue being recognized at a point-in-time when the repair and maintenance is completed.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-4.5pt;">&#xa0;</p>
   <div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt">
    <div class="PGNUM" style="text-align: center; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
     <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"></em>
    </div>
   </div>
   <ix:exclude>
    <div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt">
     <div class="PGNUM" style="text-align: center; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
      <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">8</em>
     </div>
     <hr style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always; border: none; width: 100%; height: 2px; color: #000000; background-color: #000000" />
     <div class="PGHDR" style="text-align: left; width: 100%">
       &#xa0;
     </div>
    </div> <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&#xa0;</p></ix:exclude>
   <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left"></p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">The singular performance obligation of our customer repair and maintenance equipment service contracts is the performance of the repair and maintenance with revenue being recognized over the time the service is expected to be performed. Our customers are billed for service contracts in advance of performance and therefore we have contract liability on our balance sheet.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; ">Significant Payment Terms</span></p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">In general, within our customer contracts, the purchase order identifies the product, quantity, price, pick-up allowances, payment terms and final delivery terms. Although some payment terms <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> may </em>be more extended, presently the majority of our payment terms are <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">30</em> days. As a result, we have used the available practical expedient and, consequently, do <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">not</em> adjust our revenues for the effects of a significant financing component.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;"><i><b>&#xa0;</b></i></p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; ">Shipping </span></p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">All amounts billed to customers related to shipping and handling are classified as revenues; therefore, we recognize revenue for shipping and handling fees at the time the products are shipped or when services are performed. The cost of shipping products to the customer is recognized at the time the products are shipped to the customer and our policy is to classify them as Distribution expenses.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:22.5pt;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; ">Variable Consideration</span></p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">In addition to fixed contract consideration, our contracts include some form of variable consideration, including sales discounts, trade promotions and certain other sales and consumer incentives, including rebates and coupon redemptions. In general, variable consideration is treated as a reduction in revenue when the related revenue is recognized. Depending on the specific type of variable consideration, we use the most likely amount method to determine the variable consideration. We believe there will be <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">no</em> significant changes to our estimates of variable consideration when any related uncertainties are resolved with our customers. We review and update our estimates and related accruals of variable consideration each period based on historical experience. Our recorded liability for allowances, end-user pricing adjustments and trade spending was approximately $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862403" contextRef="i_2019-12-28" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="-5" name="jjsf:ContractWithCustomerAssetAllowanceForDeductions" scale="6">15.1</ix:nonFraction> million at <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> December 28, 2019 </em>and $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862404" contextRef="i_2019-09-28" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="-5" name="jjsf:ContractWithCustomerAssetAllowanceForDeductions" scale="6">14.8</ix:nonFraction> million at <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> September 28, 2019.</em></p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt">
    <div class="PGNUM" style="text-align: center; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
     <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"></em>
    </div>
   </div>
   <ix:exclude>
    <div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt">
     <div class="PGNUM" style="text-align: center; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
      <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">9</em>
     </div>
     <hr style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always; border: none; width: 100%; height: 2px; color: #000000; background-color: #000000" />
     <div class="PGHDR" style="text-align: left; width: 100%">
       &#xa0;
     </div>
    </div> <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&#xa0;</p></ix:exclude>
   <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left"></p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; ">Warranties &amp; Returns</span></p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">We provide all customers with a standard or assurance type warranty. Either stated or implied, we provide assurance the related products will comply with all agreed-upon specifications and other warranties provided under the law. <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">No</em> services beyond an assurance warranty are provided to our customers.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">We do <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">not</em> grant a general right of return. However, customers <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> may </em>return defective or non-conforming products. Customer remedies <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> may </em>include either a cash refund or an exchange of the product. We do <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">not</em> estimate a right of return and related refund liability as returns of our products are rare.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; ">Contract Balances</span></p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">Our customers are billed for service contracts in advance of performance and therefore we have contract liability on our balance sheet as follows:</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:130.5pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-72pt;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>

   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; ">Disaggregation of Revenue</span></p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">See Note <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">9</em> for disaggregation of our net sales by class of similar product and type of customer.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:22.5pt;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; ">Allowance for Doubtful Receivables </span></p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:22.5pt;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">We provide an allowance for doubtful receivables after taking into consideration historical experience and other factors. The allowance for doubtful receivables was $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862410" contextRef="i_2019-12-28" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:AllowanceForDoubtfulAccountsReceivable" scale="0">465,000</ix:nonFraction> and $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862411" contextRef="i_2019-09-28" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:AllowanceForDoubtfulAccountsReceivable" scale="0">572,000</ix:nonFraction> at <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> December 28, 2019 </em>and <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> September 28, 2019, </em>respectively.</p>

      <td> <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">Depreciation of equipment and buildings is provided for by the straight-line method over the assets&#x2019; estimated useful lives. Amortization of improvements is provided for by the straight-line method over the term of the lease or the assets&#x2019; estimated useful lives, whichever is shorter. Licenses and rights, customer relationships and non-compete agreements arising from acquisitions are amortized by the straight-line method over periods ranging from <span style="-sec-ix-hidden:c54862421">2</span> to <span style="-sec-ix-hidden:c54862422">20</span> years. Depreciation expense was $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862423" contextRef="d_2019-09-29_2019-12-28" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:Depreciation" scale="0">11,887,000</ix:nonFraction> and $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862424" contextRef="d_2018-09-30_2018-12-29" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:Depreciation" scale="0">10,774,000</ix:nonFraction> for the <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">three</em> months ended <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> December 28, 2019 </em>and <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> December 29, 2018, </em>respectively.</p> </td>

     <tr style="vertical-align: top;">
      <td style="width: 54pt;"> <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">Note <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">4</em></p> </td>
      <td> <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">Basic earnings per common share (EPS) excludes dilution and is computed by dividing income available to common shareholders by the weighted average common shares outstanding during the period. Diluted EPS takes into consideration the potential dilution that could occur if securities (stock options) or other contracts to issue common stock were exercised and converted into common stock. Our calculation of EPS is as follows:</p> </td>

   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:54pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-54pt;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:54pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">The fair value of each option grant is estimated on the date of grant using the Black-Scholes options-pricing model.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:54pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:54pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">The Company did <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"><span style="-sec-ix-hidden:c54862460">not</span></em> grant any stock options during the fiscal year <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">2020</em> <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">three</em> month period.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:54pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:54pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">During the fiscal year <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">2019</em> <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">three</em> month period, the Company granted <ix:nonFraction id="c54862465" contextRef="d_2018-09-30_2018-12-29" unitRef="Share" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:ShareBasedCompensationArrangementByShareBasedPaymentAwardOptionsGrantsInPeriodGross" scale="0">1,000</ix:nonFraction> stock options. The weighted-average grant date fair value of these options was $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862466" contextRef="d_2018-09-30_2018-12-29" unitRef="USDPerShare" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:ShareBasedCompensationArrangementByShareBasedPaymentAwardOptionsGrantsInPeriodWeightedAverageGrantDateFairValue" scale="0">27.09</ix:nonFraction></p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:54pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">Expected volatility is based on the historical volatility of the price of our common shares over the past <span style="-sec-ix-hidden:c54862467">51</span> months for <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">5</em> year options and <span style="-sec-ix-hidden:c54862469">10</span> years for <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">10</em> year options. We use historical information to estimate expected life and forfeitures within the valuation model. The expected term of awards represents the period of time that options granted are expected to be outstanding. The risk-free rate for periods within the expected life of the option is based on the U.S. Treasury yield curve in effect at the time of grant. Compensation cost is recognized using a straight-line method over the vesting or service period and is net of estimated forfeitures.</p>
  </ix:nonNumeric>
  <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;">&#xa0;</p>
  <div>
    &#xa0;
  </div>
  <ix:nonNumeric contextRef="d_2019-09-29_2019-12-28" name="us-gaap:IncomeTaxDisclosureTextBlock" id="c1406236" escape="true">
   <table style="width:100%;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td style="width:54pt;vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">Note <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">6</em></p> </td>
      <td style="vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">We account for our income taxes under the liability method. Under the liability method, deferred tax assets and liabilities are determined based on the difference between the financial statement and tax bases of assets and liabilities as measured by the enacted tax rates that will be in effect when these differences reverse.&#xa0; Deferred tax expense is the result of changes in deferred tax assets and liabilities.</p> </td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:justify;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">Additionally, we recognize a liability for income taxes and associated penalties and interest for tax positions taken or expected to be taken in a tax return which are more likely than <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">not</em> to be overturned by taxing authorities (&#x201c;uncertain tax positions&#x201d;).&#xa0;&#xa0;We have <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">not</em> recognized a tax benefit in our financial statements&#xa0;for these uncertain tax positions.&#xa0;&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">The total amount of gross unrecognized tax benefits is $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862482" contextRef="i_2019-12-28" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:UnrecognizedTaxBenefitsThatWouldImpactEffectiveTaxRate" scale="0">414,000</ix:nonFraction> on both <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> December 28, 2019 </em>and <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> September 28, 2019, </em>all of which would impact our effective tax rate over time, if recognized. We recognize interest and penalties related to uncertain tax positions as a part of the provision for income taxes. As of <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> December 28, 2019 </em>and <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> September 28, 2019, </em>the Company has $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862484" contextRef="i_2019-12-28" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:UnrecognizedTaxBenefitsIncomeTaxPenaltiesAndInterestAccrued" scale="0">279,000</ix:nonFraction> of accrued interest and penalties.</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;"><br /> In addition to our federal tax return and tax returns for&#xa0;Mexico and Canada, we file tax returns in&#xa0;all states that have a corporate income tax with virtually all open for examination for <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">three</em> to <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">four</em> years.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:49.5pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">Net earnings in last year&#x2019;s quarter benefitted by a reduction of approximately $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862488" contextRef="d_2018-09-30_2018-12-29" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:IncomeTaxReconciliationRepatriationOfForeignEarnings" scale="0">900,000</ix:nonFraction> in tax as the provision for the <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">one</em> time repatriation tax as a result of the Tax Cuts and Job Act of <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">2017</em> was reduced as the amount recorded the year prior was an estimate. Excluding the reduction in the provision for the <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">one</em> time repatriation tax, our effective tax rate was <ix:nonFraction id="c54862492" contextRef="d_2018-09-30_2018-12-29" unitRef="Pure" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="2" name="us-gaap:EffectiveIncomeTaxRateContinuingOperations" scale="-2">28.0</ix:nonFraction>% in last year&#x2019;s quarter. &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;"></p><ix:exclude><p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt">
    <div class="PGNUM" style="text-align: center; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
     <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">12</em>

  <ix:nonNumeric contextRef="d_2019-09-29_2019-12-28" name="us-gaap:NewAccountingPronouncementsAndChangesInAccountingPrinciplesTextBlock" id="c1406237" escape="true">
   <table style="width: 100%; text-indent: 0px;" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
    <tbody>
     <tr style="vertical-align: top;">
      <td style="width: 54pt;"> <p style="margin: 0pt; text-align: left; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">Note <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">7</em></p> </td>
      <td> <p style="margin: 0pt; text-align: left; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">In <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> February 2016, </em>the FASB issued guidance on lease accounting which requires that an entity recognize most leases on its balance sheet. The guidance retains a dual lease accounting model for purposes of income statement recognition, continuing the distinction between what are currently known as &#x201c;capital&#x201d; and &#x201c;operating&#x201d; leases for lessees. We adopted the guidance on <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> September 29, 2019 </em>using this alternate transition method, but we did <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">not</em> record a cumulative-effect adjustment from initially applying the standard. We elected the package of practical expedients that permits us <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">not</em> to reassess our prior conclusions about lease identification, lease classification and initial direct costs and made an accounting policy election to exclude short-term leases with an initial term of <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">12</em> months or less from our Consolidated Balance Sheets. We have completed the implementation of a lease accounting system to enable the preparation of financial information and have implemented relevant accounting policies and internal controls surrounding the lease accounting process. As a result of adoption, we recognized a right-of-use asset and lease liability of $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862499" contextRef="i_2019-07-01_AdjustmentsForNewAccountingPronouncementsAxis-AccountingStandardsUpdate201602Member" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="-6" name="jjsf:LeaseRightOfUseAsset" scale="6">71</ix:nonFraction> million and $<ix:nonFraction id="c54863744" contextRef="i_2017-07-01_AdjustmentsForNewAccountingPronouncementsAxis-AccountingStandardsUpdate201602Member" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="-6" name="jjsf:LeaseLiability" scale="6">72</ix:nonFraction> million, respectively. The right-of-use asset balance reflects the reclassification of deferred rent and prepaid rent against the initial asset. The adoption did <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">not</em> impact our results of operations or cash flows. See additional lease disclosures in Note <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">14.</em></p> <p style="margin: 0pt; text-align: left; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">&#xa0;</p> <p style="margin: 0pt; text-align: left; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;">In <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> June 2016, </em>the FASB issued guidance to update the methodology used to measure current expected credit losses ( CECL ). This guidance applies to financial assets measured at amortized cost, including loans, held-to-maturity debt securities, net investments in leases, and trade accounts receivable as well as certain off-balance sheet credit exposures, such as loan commitments. This guidance &#xa0;replaces the current incurred loss impairment methodology with a methodology to reflect CECL and requires consideration of a broader range of reasonable and supportable information to explain credit loss estimates. The guidance must be adopted using a modified retrospective transition method through a cumulative-effect adjustment to retained earnings/(deficit) in the period of adoption. This guidance will be effective beginning in the <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">first</em> quarter of our fiscal year <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">2021.</em> Early adoption is permitted. We are currently evaluating the impact this guidance will have on our financial statements and related disclosures.</p> </td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table>
  </ix:nonNumeric>

    &#xa0;

  <ix:nonNumeric contextRef="d_2019-09-29_2019-12-28" name="us-gaap:SegmentReportingDisclosureTextBlock" id="c1406240" escape="true">
   <table style="width:100%;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td style="width:54pt;vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">Note <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">9</em></p> </td>
      <td style="vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">We principally sell our products to the food service and retail supermarket industries. Sales and results of our frozen beverages business are monitored separately from the balance of our food service business because of different distribution and capital requirements. We maintain separate and discrete financial information for the <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">three</em> operating segments mentioned above which is available to our Chief Operating Decision Makers.</p> </td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:54pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">Our <ix:nonFraction id="c54862515" contextRef="d_2019-09-29_2019-12-28" unitRef="Pure" format="ixt-sec:numwordsen" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:NumberOfReportableSegments" scale="0">three</ix:nonFraction> reportable segments are Food Service, Retail Supermarkets and Frozen Beverages. All inter-segment net sales and expenses have been eliminated in computing net sales and operating income. These segments are described below.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">Food Service</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">The primary products sold by the food service group are soft pretzels, frozen juice treats and desserts, churros, dough enrobed handheld products and baked goods. Our customers in the food service industry include snack bars and food stands in chain, department and discount stores; malls and shopping centers; fast food outlets; stadiums and sports arenas; leisure and<b> </b>theme parks; convenience stores; movie theatres; warehouse club stores; schools, colleges and other institutions. Within the food service industry, our products are purchased by the consumer primarily for consumption at the point-of-sale.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:center;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">Retail Supermarkets</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;"><b>&#xa0;</b></p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">The primary products sold to the retail supermarket channel are soft pretzel products &#x2013; including SUPERPRETZEL, frozen juice treats and desserts including LUIGI&#x2019;S Real Italian Ice, MINUTE MAID Juice Bars and Soft Frozen Lemonade, WHOLE FRUIT frozen fruit bars and sorbet, PHILLY SWIRL cups and sticks, ICEE Squeeze-Up Tubes and dough enrobed handheld products including PATIO burritos. Within the retail supermarket channel, our frozen and prepackaged products are purchased by the consumer for consumption at home.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:54pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">Frozen Beverages</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:54pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">We sell frozen beverages and related products to the food service industry primarily under the names ICEE, SLUSH PUPPIE and PARROT ICE in the United States, Mexico and Canada. We also provide repair and maintenance service to customers for customers&#x2019; owned equipment.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:54pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt">
    <div class="PGNUM" style="text-align: center; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
     <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"></em>
    </div>
   </div>
   <ix:exclude>
    <div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt">
     <div class="PGNUM" style="text-align: center; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
      <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">13</em>
     </div>
     <hr style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always; border: none; width: 100%; height: 2px; color: #000000; background-color: #000000" />
     <div class="PGHDR" style="text-align: left; width: 100%">
       &#xa0;
     </div>
    </div> <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p></ix:exclude>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;"></p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left;">The Chief Operating Decision Maker for Food Service and Retail Supermarkets and the Chief Operating Decision Maker for Frozen Beverages monthly review detailed operating income statements and sales reports in order to assess performance and allocate resources to each individual segment.&#xa0;Sales and operating income are key variables monitored by the Chief Operating Decision Makers and management when determining each segment&#x2019;s and the company&#x2019;s financial condition and operating performance.&#xa0;In addition, the Chief Operating Decision Makers review and evaluate depreciation, capital spending and assets of each segment on a quarterly basis to monitor cash flow and asset needs of each segment. Due to a change in management and the reporting of our MARYB&#x2019;s biscuit operations, which had sales and operating income of $<ix:nonFraction id="c54863754" contextRef="d_2018-09-30_2019-09-28_ProductOrServiceAxis-MARYBsBiscuitOperationsMember" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:RevenueFromContractWithCustomerIncludingAssessedTax" scale="0">25,316,000</ix:nonFraction> and $<ix:nonFraction id="c54863755" contextRef="d_2018-09-30_2019-09-28_ProductOrServiceAxis-MARYBsBiscuitOperationsMember" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:OperatingIncomeLoss" scale="0">1,584,000</ix:nonFraction>, respectively, in our <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">2019</em> fiscal year, we have reclassified the operations from our Food Service segment to our Retail Supermarket segment, which is reflected in both periods reported.&#xa0;Information regarding the operations in these <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">three</em> reportable segments is as follows:</p>
   <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&#xa0;</p>

     <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"></em></div></div><ix:exclude><div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt"><div class="PGNUM" style="text-align: center; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">15</em>

   </div>
   <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&#xa0;</p></ix:exclude><p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left"></p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">Fully amortized intangible assets have been removed from the <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> December 28, 2019 </em>amounts. Intangible assets of $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862602" contextRef="d_2019-09-29_2019-12-28_BusinessAcquisitionAxis-ICEEDistributorMember_StatementBusinessSegmentsAxis-FrozenBeveragesMember" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:IndefinitelivedIntangibleAssetsAcquired" scale="0">21,769,000</ix:nonFraction> were added in the frozen beverages segment from the acquisition of ICEE Distributors.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">Amortizing intangible assets are being amortized by the straight-line method over periods ranging from <span style="-sec-ix-hidden:c54862603">2</span> to <span style="-sec-ix-hidden:c54862604">20</span> years and amortization expense is reflected throughout operating expenses. Aggregate amortization expense of intangible assets for the <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">three</em> months ended <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> December 28, 2019 </em>and <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> December 29, 2018 </em>was $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862606" contextRef="d_2019-09-29_2019-12-28" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:AmortizationOfIntangibleAssets" scale="0">843,000</ix:nonFraction> and $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862607" contextRef="d_2018-09-30_2018-12-29" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:AmortizationOfIntangibleAssets" scale="0">855,000</ix:nonFraction>, respectively.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">Estimated amortization expense for the next <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">five</em> fiscal years is approximately $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862609" contextRef="i_2019-12-28" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:FiniteLivedIntangibleAssetsAmortizationExpenseRemainderOfFiscalYear" scale="0">3,100,000</ix:nonFraction> in <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">2020,</em> $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862611" contextRef="i_2019-12-28" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:FiniteLivedIntangibleAssetsAmortizationExpenseYearTwo" scale="0">2,500,000</ix:nonFraction> in <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">2021,</em> $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862613" contextRef="i_2019-12-28" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:FiniteLivedIntangibleAssetsAmortizationExpenseYearThree" scale="0">2,300,000</ix:nonFraction> in <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">2022,</em> $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862615" contextRef="i_2019-12-28" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:FiniteLivedIntangibleAssetsAmortizationExpenseYearFour" scale="0">2,300,000</ix:nonFraction> in <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">2023</em> and $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862617" contextRef="i_2019-12-28" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:FiniteLivedIntangibleAssetsAmortizationExpenseYearFive" scale="0">2,000,000</ix:nonFraction> in <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">2024.</em> The weighted amortization period of the intangible assets is <span style="-sec-ix-hidden:c54862619">10.7</span> years.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>

  </div>
  <ix:nonNumeric contextRef="d_2019-09-29_2019-12-28" name="us-gaap:FairValueDisclosuresTextBlock" id="c1406245" escape="true">
   <table style="width: 100%; text-indent: 0px;" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
    <tbody>
     <tr style="vertical-align: top;">
      <td style="width: 54pt;"> <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">Note <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">11</em></p> </td>
      <td> <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">We have classified our investment securities as marketable securities held to maturity and available for sale. The FASB defines fair value as the price that would be received from selling an asset or paid to transfer a liability in an orderly transaction between market participants. As such, fair value is a market-based measurement that should be determined based on assumptions that market participants would use in pricing an asset or liability. As a basis for considering such assumptions, the FASB has established <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">three</em> levels of inputs that <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> may </em>be used to measure fair value:</p> </td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table>
   <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&#xa0;</p>
   <table style="width:100%;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td style="width:72pt;vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">Level <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">1</em></p> </td>
      <td style="vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">Observable input such as quoted prices in active markets for identical assets or liabilities;</p> </td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table>
   <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&#xa0;</p>
   <table style="width:100%;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td style="width:72pt;vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">Level <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">2</em></p> </td>
      <td style="vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">Observable inputs, other than Level <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">1</em> inputs in active markets, that are observable either directly or indirectly; and</p> </td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table>
   <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&#xa0;</p>
   <table style="width:100%;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
    <tbody>
     <tr>
      <td style="width:72pt;vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">Level <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">3</em></p> </td>
      <td style="vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;">Unobservable inputs for which there is little or <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">no</em> market data, which require the reporting entity to&#xa0;develop its own assumptions.</p> </td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:72pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;"></p><ix:exclude><p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:center;">&#xa0;</p>
   <div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt">
    <div class="PGNUM" style="text-align: center; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
     <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">16</em>
    </div>
    <hr style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always; border: none; width: 100%; height: 2px; color: #000000; background-color: #000000" />
    <div class="PGHDR" style="text-align: left; width: 100%">
      &#xa0;
    </div>
   </div>
   <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&#xa0;</p></ix:exclude><p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left"></p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">Marketable securities held to maturity and available for sale consist primarily of investments in mutual funds, preferred stock and corporate bonds.&#xa0; The fair values of mutual funds are based on quoted market prices in active markets and are classified within Level <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">1</em> of the fair value hierarchy. &#xa0;The fair values of preferred stock, corporate bonds and certificates of deposit are based on quoted prices for identical or similar instruments in markets that are <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">not</em> active.&#xa0; As a result, preferred stock, corporate bonds and certificates of deposit are classified within Level <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">2</em> of the fair value hierarchy.&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:63pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-63pt;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">The amortized cost, unrealized gains and losses, and fair market values of our investment securities held to maturity at <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> December 28, 2019 </em>are summarized as follows:</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>

   </ix:continuation>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">The mutual funds seek current income with an emphasis on maintaining low volatility and overall moderate duration. The Fixed-to-Floating Perpetual Preferred Stock generate fixed income to call dates in <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">2020</em> and <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">2025</em> and then income is based on a spread above LIBOR if the securities are <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">not</em> called. The mutual funds and Fixed-to-Floating Perpetual Preferred Stock do <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">not</em> have contractual maturities; however, we classify them as long term assets as it is our intent to hold them for a period of over <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">one</em> year, although we <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> may </em>sell some or all of them depending on presently unanticipated needs for liquidity or market conditions. The corporate bonds generate fixed income to maturity dates in <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">2020</em> through <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">2024,</em> with $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862716" contextRef="i_2019-12-28_InvestmentTypeAxis-CorporateBondSecuritiesMember" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="-6" name="us-gaap:HeldToMaturitySecurities" scale="6">106</ix:nonFraction> million maturing within <span style="-sec-ix-hidden:c54862717">2</span> years. Our expectation is that we will hold the corporate bonds to their maturity dates and redeem them at our amortized cost.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">The amortized cost, unrealized gains and losses, and fair market values of our investment securities held to maturity at <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> September 28, 2019 </em>are summarized as follows:</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>

   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">Proceeds from the redemption and sale of marketable securities were $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862719" contextRef="d_2019-09-29_2019-12-28" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:ProceedsFromSaleAndMaturityOfMarketableSecurities" scale="0">18,782,000</ix:nonFraction> in the <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">three</em> months ended <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> December 28, 2019 </em>and $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862721" contextRef="d_2018-09-30_2018-12-29" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:ProceedsFromSaleAndMaturityOfMarketableSecurities" scale="0">17,125,000</ix:nonFraction> in the <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">three</em> ended <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> December 29, 2018, </em>respectively. Losses of $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862723" contextRef="d_2019-09-29_2019-12-28" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:MarketableSecuritiesGainLoss" sign="-" scale="0">11,000</ix:nonFraction> and $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862724" contextRef="d_2018-09-30_2018-12-29" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:MarketableSecuritiesGainLoss" sign="-" scale="0">1,027,000</ix:nonFraction> were recorded in the <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">three</em> months ended <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> December 28, 2019 </em>and <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> December 28, 2018, </em>respectively, which included unrealized gains on marketable securities of $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862726" contextRef="d_2019-09-29_2019-12-28" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:MarketableSecuritiesUnrealizedGainLoss" scale="0">71,000</ix:nonFraction> and unrealized losses on marketable securities of $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862727" contextRef="d_2018-09-30_2018-12-29" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:MarketableSecuritiesUnrealizedGainLoss" sign="-" scale="0">1,027,000</ix:nonFraction> in the <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">three</em> months ended <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> December 28, 2019 </em>and <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> December 29, 2018, </em>respectively.        <td style="width: 15%; text-align: right; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin-left: 0pt; border-bottom: 3px double rgb(0, 0, 0);"><ix:nonFraction id="c54862894" contextRef="i_2019-10-01_BusinessAcquisitionAxis-ICEEDistributorMember" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="-4" name="us-gaap:BusinessCombinationRecognizedIdentifiableAssetsAcquiredGoodwillAndLiabilitiesAssumedNet" scale="3">44,970</ix:nonFraction></td>
       <td style="width: 1%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; padding-bottom: 3px; margin-left: 0pt;">&#xa0;</td>
      </tr>
     </tbody>
    </table>
   </ix:nonNumeric>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">The goodwill recognized is attributable to the assembled workforce of ICEE Distributors and certain other strategic intangible assets that do <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">not</em> meet the requirements for recognition separate and apart from goodwill.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:58.5pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">Acquisition costs of $<ix:nonFraction id="c54862885" contextRef="d_2019-12-28_2019-12-28_BusinessAcquisitionAxis-ICEEDistributorMember" unitRef="USD" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="INF" name="us-gaap:BusinessCombinationAcquisitionRelatedCosts" scale="0">36,000</ix:nonFraction> are included in other general expense for the <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">three</em> months ended <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> December 28, 2019.</em></p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:58.5pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align: left;">Our unaudited proforma results, giving effect to this acquisition and assuming an acquisition date of <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> September 29, 2018, </em>would have been:</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:58.5pt;margin-right:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>

  <ix:nonNumeric contextRef="d_2019-09-29_2019-12-28" name="jjsf:LesseeLeasesTextBlock" id="c1406257" escape="true">
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">Note <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">14</em> &#x2013;&#xa0;Leases</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 27pt;">General Lease Description</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 27pt;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 54pt;">We have operating leases with initial noncancelable lease terms in excess of <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">one</em> year covering the rental of various facilities and equipment. Certain of these leases contain renewal options and some provide options to purchase during the lease term. Our operating leases include leases for real estate for some of our office and manufacturing facilities as well as manufacturing and non-manufacturing equipment used in our business. The remaining lease terms for these operating leases range from&#xa0;<span style="-sec-ix-hidden:c54862901">1</span>&#xa0;month&#xa0;to&#xa0;<ix:nonNumeric contextRef="d_2019-09-29_2019-12-28_RangeAxis-MaximumMember" name="jjsf:LesseeOperatingLeaseRemainingLeaseTerm" id="c54862902" format="ixt-sec:duryear">13</ix:nonNumeric> years.</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 45pt;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 54pt;">We have finance leases with initial noncancelable lease terms in excess of <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">one</em> year covering the rental of various equipment. These leases are generally for manufacturing and non-manufacturing equipment used in our business. The remaining lease terms for these finance leases range from <ix:nonNumeric contextRef="d_2019-09-29_2019-12-28_RangeAxis-MinimumMember" name="jjsf:LesseeFinanceLeaseRemainingLeaseTerm" id="c54862904" format="ixt-sec:duryear">1</ix:nonNumeric> year to&#xa0;<ix:nonNumeric contextRef="d_2019-09-29_2019-12-28_RangeAxis-MaximumMember" name="jjsf:LesseeFinanceLeaseRemainingLeaseTerm" id="c54862905" format="ixt-sec:duryear">6</ix:nonNumeric>&#xa0;years.&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;</p>
   <div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt">
    <div class="PGNUM" style="text-align: center; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
     <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"></em></div></div><ix:exclude><div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt"><div class="PGNUM" style="text-align: center; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">20</em>
    </div>
    <hr style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always; border: none; width: 100%; height: 2px; color: #000000; background-color: #000000" />
    <div class="PGHDR" style="text-align: left; width: 100%">
      &#xa0;
    </div>
   </div>
   <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&#xa0;</p></ix:exclude><p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left"></p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 27pt;">Significant Assumptions and Judgments</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 27pt;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 27pt;">Contract Contains a Lease</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 54pt;">In evaluating our contracts to determine whether a contract is or contains a lease, we considered the following:&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 45pt;">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#x2022;&#xa0; &#xa0; &#xa0; &#xa0; &#xa0;Whether explicitly or implicitly identified assets have been deployed in the contract; and</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#x2022;&#xa0; &#xa0; &#xa0; &#xa0; &#xa0;Whether we obtain substantially all of the economic benefits from the use of that underlying asset, and we can direct how and for what purpose the asset is used during the term of the contract.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 27pt;">Allocation of Consideration</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 27pt;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 54pt;">In determining how to allocate consideration between lease and non-lease components in a contract that was deemed to contain a lease, we used judgment and consistent application of assumptions to reasonably allocate the consideration.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 27pt;">Options to Extend or Terminate Leases</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 54pt;">We have leases which contain options to extend or terminate the leases. On a lease-by-lease basis, we have determined if the extension should be considered reasonably certain to be exercised and thus a right-of-use asset and a lease liability should be recorded.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 27pt;">Discount Rate</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 54pt;">The discount rate for leases, if <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">not</em> explicitly stated in the lease, is the incremental borrowing rate, which is the rate of interest that we would have to pay to borrow on a collateralized basis over a similar term an amount equal to the lease payments in a similar economic environment.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 54pt;">We used the discount rate to calculate the present value of the lease liability at the date of adoption. In the development of the discount rate, we considered our incremental borrowing rate as provided by our lender which was based on cash collateral and credit risk specific to us, and our lease portfolio characteristics.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 54pt;">As of&#xa0;<em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"> September&#xa0;</em><em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">29,</em> <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">2019,</em> the weighted-average discount rate of our operating and finance leases was <ix:nonFraction id="c54862910" contextRef="i_2019-12-28" unitRef="Pure" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="3" name="us-gaap:OperatingLeaseWeightedAverageDiscountRatePercent" scale="-2">3.3</ix:nonFraction>% and <ix:nonFraction id="c54862911" contextRef="i_2019-12-28" unitRef="Pure" format="ixt:numdotdecimal" decimals="3" name="us-gaap:FinanceLeaseWeightedAverageDiscountRatePercent" scale="-2">3.1</ix:nonFraction>%, respectively.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 27pt;">Practical Expedients and Accounting Policy Elections</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 54pt;">We elected the package of practical expedients that permits us <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">not</em> to reassess our prior conclusions about lease&#xa0;identification, lease classification and initial direct costs and made an accounting policy election to exclude short-term leases with an initial term of <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">12</em> months or less from our Consolidated Balance Sheets.</p>
   <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-size:10pt;margin:0pt;text-align:left;">&#xa0;</p>
   <div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt">
    <div class="PGNUM" style="text-align: center; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
     <em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;"></em></div></div><ix:exclude><div class="PGBK" style="width: 100%; margin-left: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt"><div class="PGNUM" style="text-align: center; width: 100%; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><em style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: normal;">21</em>
    </div>
    <hr style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always; border: none; width: 100%; height: 2px; color: #000000; background-color: #000000" />

       <td style="width: 1%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin-left: 0pt;">&#xa0;</td>
